3
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:20,600
Dad...

4
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:22,300
It's too much.

5
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,500
Well, it's yours, baby.

6
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:30,100
They have public transportation
in Philadelphia, you know.

7
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:31,400
Now you won't
have to use it.

8
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,100
Dad, you've got to
stop worrying about me.

9
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:33,900
I'm gonna be fine.

10
00:00:34,100 --> 00:00:36,100
Your degree, your brains...

11
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:38,100
you could do anything you want.

12
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:40,400
Law school, politics, Wall Street...

13
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:42,000
But Dad...

14
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:44,400
this is what I want.

15
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:00,300
Laura McKinney ?

16
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:02,300
I'm Margaret Trudlow.
You're late.

17
00:01:02,300 --> 00:01:04,200
Sorry. Got a little lost.

18
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:06,800
We have an unexpected
change in faculty.

19
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:09,800
One of our US History teachers,
Mr. Hack, had an incident.

20
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:10,900
"Incident" ?

21
00:01:10,900 --> 00:01:12,100
Run-in with some
seniors last year.

22
00:01:12,100 --> 00:01:13,300
Nothing for you
to worry about,

23
00:01:13,300 --> 00:01:14,600
but you'll cover
his class this year.

24
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:16,600
I'm supposed to teach English.

25
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:19,600
I'm not familiar
with US History.

26
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:21,200
Neither are the students.

27
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:23,700
No problem.

28
00:01:24,100 --> 00:01:25,100
Ready for the challenge.

29
00:01:25,100 --> 00:01:26,800
That's the Ivy League spirit.

30
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:28,400
This is yours.

31
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:41,400
My classroom's next door
if you have any issues,

32
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:43,300
but I'm sure you won't.

33
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:44,600
Any advice ?

34
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:46,800
Show no fear.

35
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:52,800
Hi, class.

36
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,400
My name's Miss McKinney.

37
00:01:57,100 --> 00:01:58,700
Can you turn that down, please ?

38
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:00,700
Excuse me.
Settle down, guys.

39
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,400
Can you please take your seat ?

40
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:03,600
Hey !

41
00:02:07,800 --> 00:02:10,200
Stop it !
Stop it !

42
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:56,500
Someone helping you ?

43
00:02:56,700 --> 00:02:59,100
They told me to wait for
one of those detectives.

44
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:00,400
One sec.

45
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:15,200
Hmm, they look pretty busy.

46
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:16,600
Why don't you talk to me ?

47
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:17,700
Darnell Brent.

48
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:19,400
I'm Detective Rush.

49
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:22,500
Think I have evidence
on Laura McKinney's murder.

50
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,000
She was my teacher
at Reeves High,

51
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,900
got shot outside
the school in 1991.

52
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,700
They said it was
a carjacking gone wrong.

53
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,100
You know different ?

54
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:34,400
Just got my teaching credential.

55
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:36,100
Started at Reeves last week.

56
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:37,700
Coincidence ?

57
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,300
She's the reason I'm doing it.

58
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:41,100
Always challenged us
to make a difference.

59
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:42,600
Figured it was
about time I tried.

60
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:44,100
What'd you find, Darnell ?

61
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:46,500
So I'm there this weekend,
getting my classroom ready.

62
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,600
Found this old,
sturdy desk in storage

63
00:03:48,601 --> 00:03:50,301
they used to have
when I was a student.

64
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,500
I was going through the drawers,

65
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:54,100
and I find these.

66
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:57,100
They're her keys,
including her car keys.

67
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:59,000
Miss McKinney wouldn't have left
the classroom without them,

68
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,400
never mind the building.

69
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:02,400
People forget their keys
all the time.

70
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,700
I've worked at the school two days.

71
00:04:03,700 --> 00:04:06,100
First thing you learn, don't go
anywhere without your keys.

72
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:07,000
The school's locked down ?

73
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:07,900
Especially at night.

74
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:09,500
Can't get from one door
to the other without them.

75
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:11,000
Miss McKinney would've known that.

76
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:12,600
She wasn't going to her car.

77
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:14,700
So if she wasn't
headed to her car,

78
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:15,900
where was she going?

79
00:04:16,100 --> 00:04:17,300
I don't know.

80
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:20,100
I've got to say, Darnell,

81
00:04:20,300 --> 00:04:21,300
not a lot to go on.

82
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:23,700
Look, I know you're busy.

83
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,600
But I can't let this sit.

84
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,200
After everything
Miss McKinney did for me...

85
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:33,200
Sounds like
she was a special teacher.

86
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:35,700
Yeah... the best.

87
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:39,000
I owe her.

